**********SOFTWARES Requirements************

1. FastQC
2. Trimmomatic
3. Flash
4. bowtie2
5. samtools
6. Unicycler
7. seqtk
8. AlignGraph


**********Scipts Requirements**********

1. ncbi-genome-download 
2. plentyofbugs (https://github.com/nickp60/plentyofbugs)


**********Commands******

========STEP-1 Reads Processing=======

fastqc -o fastqc_output  -f fastq  Read1.fq Read2.fq (Quality check of Reads)

trimmomatic PE -threads 8 -phred33/64 Read1.fq Read2.fq output_1P.fq output_1U.fq output_2P.fq output_2U.fq ILLUMINACLIP:PATH_TO_ADAPTER_CONTAM_FILE:2:30:10 LEADING:3 TRAILING:3 SLIDINGWINDOW:4:15 MINLEN:36 (To remove low quality base pairs and adapter sequences)

fastqc -o fastqc_output  -f fastq  output_1P.fq output_2P.fq  (Quality check of Reads after Trimming)

========STEP-2 Reference Genomes Download=====

ncbi-genome-download --format fasta -l complete --species-taxids 562 bacteria (Download reference genomes of particular organism)

========STEP-3 Best Reference Genome Selection======

plentyofbugs -f output_1P.fq -r output_2P.fq -g Reference_genomes_DIR -o output (Selection of best genome based upon Mash Value)

========STEP-4 Reference Genome Validation=======

bowtie2-build -f Reference_genome reference (Indexing of reference genome)

bowtie2 -x reference -1 output_1P.fq -2 output_2P.fq -S out.sam

samtools flagstat --threads no.ofthreads out.sam (% alignment calculation)

========STEP-5 Denovo Assembly(contigs generation)======

flash output_1P.fq output_2P.fq >output (will generate notCombined and extended fastq files) 

unicycler -1 file.notCombined_1.fastq -2 file.out.notCombined_2.fastq -s file.out.extendedFrags.fastq --min_fasta_length 200 -o sample_assembly (contig.fasta generation)

========STEP-6 Reference Based Assembly(scaffolding)======

seqtk seq output_1P/2P.fq > out1/2.fa

AlignGraph --read1 out1.fa --read2 out2.fa --contig contigs.fasta --genome Reference_genome --distanceLow 100 --distanceHigh 1000 --extendedContig sample_extendedcontig.fasta --remainingContig sample_remainingcontig.fasta

